#eNCA Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - The Senzo Meyiwa murder trial took an unusual twist in court, when a second docket was revealed. It is calling for all those present at the house in which Meyiwa was killed, to be charged. READ: Meyiwa murder trial postponed to Monday The second docket lists the people in the house the day Meyiwa was shot as suspects.
Zandlile Mshololo, defence lawyer for accused number five, requested a postponement to study the second docket. Watch the video above for more details on this story. #eNCA Courtesy #DStv403